photo.description: Open 365 days a year, Bok Tower Gardens, is a &quot;must see&quot; gem. Surrounded by rolling hills of orange groves this National Historic Landmark will warm your heart with it's beautiful Olmsted gardens, the 205-foot art deco Singing Tower, and the enchanting Mediterranean Pinewood Estate. Dedicated is 1929 as a gift from Dutch immigrant Edward Bok, a Pulitzer Prize-winning author and world peace advocate, this attraction sits between Tampa and Orlando. (PhotoJulie Fletcher)

photo.description: Bok Tower in the Bok Sanctuary, Lake Wales, Florida. The centerpiece of the botanical garden (designed by Frederick Law Olmsted, Jr.), the Tower was built in the 1920s of pink Georgia marble and was dedicated by President Calvin Coolidge. It houses a carillon which is still used regularly (with daily concerts in the afternoons).
Bok Tower behind a pine forest raked through by the 2004 hurricanes.
